document.title: Maryland Physical Education Framework: Pre-Kindergarten Through High School

6E877870D3ED40A2AB6B19D86F802365.description:
Identifies and
participates in an
enjoyable activity that
prompts individual self-expression.

2AB546D77C1E4C3E86EE8C1E097C1B05.description:
Discusses how
enjoyment could be
increased in self-selected physical
activities.

535A22EFB7894B4B88B2E5C4573AB5F1.description:
Justifies that skills will
develop over time with
appropriate practice.

4FF959A8BBE84AAD92296BCB00AC0CCA.description:
Develops a plan of
action and makes
appropriate decisions
based on that plan
when faced with an
individual challenge.

39024745A1664D978934DDEC6CB60261.description:
Analyzes the
empowering
consequences of being
physically active.

238EAFFDCD0F4294908E478DAA7C5FBC.description:
Identifies the
components of health-related fitness and
explains the relationship
between fitness and
overall physical and
mental health.

632AB4D225CD4CCFA31AF91682FD4749.description: Recognizes the Value of Physical Activity

867D8450E45E42C98603B756BCE4CB28.description:
Applies rules and
etiquette by acting as
an official for modified
physical activities and
games and creating
dance routines within a
given set of parameters.

8E1EC14D7930497384191CB51D64A455.description:
Cooperates with
multiple classmates on
problem-solving
initiatives.

124884CA9B6143D3A58DFBEF62BB5501.description:
Responds appropriately
to participants’ behavior
during physical activity
by using rules and
guidelines for resolving
conflicts.

308134E27E0742908B63E815108677D2.description:
Provides
encouragement and
feedback to peers
without prompting.

BE5EFFB3EF514D1AA80A0A380D2E0DAA.description:
Uses effective self-monitoring skills to
incorporate
opportunities for
physical activity.

A06165EB9BEA467D956D2A1B8C90BD21.description:
Accepts responsibility
for improving one’s own
levels of physical
activity and fitness.

CC12364B98174DB9912E295513167B5A.description:
Employs a variety of
appropriate static
stretching techniques
for all major muscle
groups.

EF2C2E4A69114E79A40EA00B67DF16A7.description:
Uses available
technology to self-monitor quantity of
exercise needed for a
minimal health standard
and/or optimal
functioning based on
current fitness level.

FDE7E7A0633440F6809EA621C6CA8B50.description:
Compares and contrasts
health-related fitness
components.

A76583FD953B4A779142B73126114EE0.description:
Participates in
moderate to vigorous
aerobic and/or muscle
and bone-strengthening physical
activity.

4A300E067A144EBDA8C635FB92A5A0E1.description:
Plans and implements a
program of cross-training to include
aerobic, strength,
endurance, and
flexibility training.

B2F6A92FF0BD46938AD151207AD8D933.description:
Participates in a variety
of self-selected aerobic
fitness activities outside
of school such as
walking, jogging, biking,
skating, dancing, and
swimming.

67564653874C485E8F3E194C02AEE45C.description:
Develops a plan to
address one of the
barriers within one’s
family, school, or
community to
maintaining a physically
active lifestyle.

8C973E0F01C6443499A9FA7CE308C8A1.description: Health-Enhancing Level of Physical Activity and Fitness

6E880C45E40941C7996EACB5D222BD6C.description:
Implements safe
protocols in self-selected outdoor
activities.

FFF102FDAEB344329DB45F18B5B4FD17.description:
Describes and applies
mechanical advantage(s)
for a variety of
movement patterns.

0877D57057FE45FD8B0E16ECB28ED2DF.description:
Reduces open spaces in
the field by working
with teammates to
maximize coverage.

6C8E3102041947CEABE527D04BEEBB76.description:
Identifies sacrifice
situations and attempts
to advance a teammate.

91009F0A2D5F492A981B6933F05E1CE2.description:
Varies the speed, force,
and trajectory of the
shot based on location
of the object in relation
to the target.

0756F5B9358542CC95199607D59B3736.description:
Varies placement, force,
and timing of return to
prevent anticipation by
opponent.

665B2236486F4931BC01EAD457ED1642.description:
Creates open space in
net or wall games with
either a long-handled or
a short-handled
implement by varying
force or direction, or by
moving opponent from
side to side, and/or
forward and backwards.

3C2ED174385F4DD8A2BE427CDFAE3193.description:
Transitions from
offense to defense or
defense to offense by
recovering quickly,
communicating with
teammates, and
capitalizing on an
advantage.

B68F6BEB972C4BD5BA7C209C36640788.description:
Reduces open space by
not allowing the catch
(denial) and anticipating
the speed of the object
and person for the
purpose of interception
or deflection.

F5DFD33E76894463B0F7F0A22C3D1A08.description:
Reduces open space on
defense by staying on
the goal side of the
offensive player and
reducing the distance to
the opponent.

5D33A820352748FE8F2FFF0D5CFF631C.description:
Reducing Space -
Changing Size and
Shape

F333A8F98A3F4C9FB9F0A1F56DE8CC49.description:
Executes at least three
of the following
offensive tactics to
create open space:
moves to create open
space on and off the
ball; uses a variety of
passes, fakes and
pathways; give and go.

FEE82F8E69784C6A9216FAFB72C7C090.description:
Opens and closes space
during small-sided game
play with movement
concepts.

677C66B5E6F14A2BA0F06C26874D7E03.description:
Demonstrates correct
technique for basic
skills in at least two
self-selected individual
performance activities.

23BC3625CE664CFFBE814FF851F37C3B.description:
Demonstrates correct
technique for basic
skills in at least two
self-selected outdoor
activities.

719F2F8E67964B72AB9DA152FA7D53D8.description:
Catches a variety of
objects from different
trajectories and speeds
in a dynamic
environment or
modified game play
while using an
implement.

63535528FBEB4318914AA63A37A72179.description:
Catching with a Short
or Long-Handled
Implement

A706CE40C547418C8D0CF5FFC20AF8ED.description:
Strikes a pitched ball
with an implement for
power to open space in
a variety of small-sided
games.

1D84F339D5304836AF8416A9FFE094D5.description:
Consistently propels an
object with accuracy
and control for target
games.

23CD314F9FF0477AA345F8779C11A5D7.description:
Two-hand volleys with
control in a small-sided
game.

437244506D354516A8CCA2841386DD26.description:
Forehand and backhand
volleys with a mature
pattern and control
using a short-handled
implement during
modified game play.

A2838F28EE414D5893B9E6C702E623E3.description:
Transfers weight with
correct timing using
low-to-high striking
pattern with a long-handled implement on
the forehand and
backhand sides.

9D87BE493D51410AACDEC2967A306BB9.description:
Demonstrates the
mature form of
forehand and backhand
strokes with a short or
long-handled
implement with power
and accuracy in net
games.

B323A017B5384895A9C637E5F4E74189.description:
Strikes with a mature
overhand pattern in a
modified net or wall
games.

4200E64176FE45B1888AE9CC9AE6B99A.description:
Consistently executes
an underhand serve for
distance and accuracy
for net and wall games.

E1C6E390AD9244F4B3483BBE664A2C00.description:
Drop-steps in the
direction of the pass
during player-to-player
defense.

1E6301089F904A4B8356CABEA6190825.description:
Shoots on goal with a
long-handled
implement for power
and accuracy in
modified invasion
games.

D45D7473DCEF496081C850EF94AF4006.description:
Foot-dribbles or
dribbles with an
implement with control,
changing speed, and
direction during small-sided game play.

8700DF40CDC94E5AB3B50EB856CCA67F.description:
Dribbles with dominant
and non-dominant
hands using a change of
speed and direction in
small-sided game play.

EBBC786BEEA8490E82C206D16ECB499A.description:
Executes the following
offensive skills during
small-sided game play:
pivot, give and go, and
fakes.

D479EB45C7B24B44B2FA67BB1F13727B.description:
Executes at least two of
the following to create
open space during
modified game play:
pivots, fakes, jab steps,
screens.

651418C5821348CF834BAB6604DD6844.description:
Throws a leading pass
to a moving partner off
a dribble or pass.

600302DECA004D93871E1AEF3417A738.description:
Passes and receives
with an implement
while changing
direction, speed, and/or
level, with competency.

76486C9CE6A449B786E9F7EDCC8C1615.description:
Catches an object from
different trajectories
and speeds in a dynamic
environment or
modified game play.

05D0F5120D444877A90D04A49DF53742.description:
Throws with a mature
pattern for distance or
power appropriate to
the activity during
small-sided game play.

B6642B35766148D5B9023211C5009BFF.description:
Exhibits command of
rhythm and timing by
creating a movement
sequence to music as an
individual or in a group.
